p2
VParamacharya aradhana tomorrow
p3
sVnews
p4
VS ri Kanchi Math is observing the aradhana of Paramacharya from December 30. Veda parayanam, bhajans, discourses and music recitals are being held and the aradhana will conclude tomorrow, January 1, with special puja and archana.Paramacharya continues to be the guiding spirit for thousands of people, whose lives he touched in many ways.Offers solaceThe Brindavan at the Math in Kanchipuram is thronged by devotees, who go there for solace and peace. &#8220;Prayer here is sure to give strength and solution,&#8221; aver regular visitors.Periyava, as he is universally referred to, is revered by not only Hindus but people of other religions too, as was witnessed when he attained siddhi on January 9, 1994. Followers, cutting across caste, religion and nation, paid their respects as the saint shed his mortal coil on that day. Ardent devotees especially recall how the Nizam (1934), who had declared State mourning following the death of a relative, allowed the procession of Paramacharya, when he passed the region. He did not stop the play of the nagaswaram and other instruments as the entourage passed.The 17 {+t} {+h} aradhana of Mahaswami is on at the Brindavan, Sri Matam, Kanchipuram. Ekadasa Rudra Japa and special homams for the welfare of humanity will be conducted tomorrow, the aradhana day, from 7 a.m. Vasordhara Poornahuti and Mahabhishekam at the Brindavan will be performed between 12 noon and 1 p.m. Group singing of Pancharatna Kritis will start by 9 a.m.
